00:03:58.040 --> 00:03:59.340
&gt;&gt; Patricia Baine: I
guess it's good afternoon.

00:03:59.340 --> 00:04:02.160
Hi, a very warm welcome to
all of you and especially

00:04:02.160 --> 00:04:04.010
to our poets and writers.

00:04:04.010 --> 00:04:09.960
The Africa Society is a nonprofit
organization that works to educate,

00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:13.540
inform, and advocate on
behalf of Africa in order

00:04:13.540 --> 00:04:17.770
to create understanding and to
promote meaningful engagement

00:04:17.770 --> 00:04:21.860
with Africa that will encourage
partnerships on culture

00:04:21.860 --> 00:04:25.390
and education and technology
and commerce.

00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:29.460
This is why we are very supportive
of [inaudible] education.

00:04:29.460 --> 00:04:32.510
With increasing advancements
in technology that continue

00:04:32.510 --> 00:04:37.100
to bring people closer to us, we
appreciative to you, our writers

00:04:37.100 --> 00:04:42.410
and our poets for your literary
contributions that communicates

00:04:42.410 --> 00:04:47.110
and continue to interpret the
world for generations to come.

00:04:47.110 --> 00:04:48.890
We all know the power of a book

00:04:48.890 --> 00:04:52.520
and how a good book can transport
you to a different world.

00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:55.380
And while you're there, you
will inevitably learn something

00:04:55.380 --> 00:04:57.260
about the author's world.

00:04:57.260 --> 00:05:00.720
And to us, that is why African
literary work is essential

00:05:00.720 --> 00:05:03.680
in our efforts to educate
about African continents

00:05:03.680 --> 00:05:05.010
because when I was growing up,

00:05:05.010 --> 00:05:07.500
all I knew about the west
was what I read in a book.

00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:10.620
And so now, we have the same
opportunity as writers and poets

00:05:10.620 --> 00:05:14.700
to communicate our world
to the rest of the world.

00:05:14.700 --> 00:05:18.740
We will, at some point here
today, have some students who are

00:05:18.740 --> 00:05:24.770 position:56%
on their way [laughter] and they are
extraordinary educator who's part

00:05:24.770 --> 00:05:28.320
of one of our other flagship
programs, Teach Africa.

00:05:28.320 --> 00:05:30.240
They are from the School
Without Walls.

00:05:30.240 --> 00:05:33.740
They are very excited to be here
today so when they are speaking

00:05:33.740 --> 00:05:36.930
to you, you'll understand
why they are very animated.

00:05:36.930 --> 00:05:40.280
They are all, as I understand
it, aspiring writers.

00:05:40.280 --> 00:05:42.720
So enjoy the program and
it's good to meet all of you.

00:05:42.720 --> 00:05:44.520
Thank you.

00:05:44.520 --> 00:05:51.530
