00:27:38.310 --> 00:27:41.380 position:56%
And so it's easy to do them quickly.

00:27:41.380 --> 00:27:47.730
But at the center, I don't think
any of us ever lose sight of --

00:27:47.730 --> 00:27:49.030
&gt;&gt; Mary-Jane Deeb: The whole.

00:27:49.030 --> 00:27:51.030
&gt;&gt; Matthew Shenoda: -- of the
core, of the work of the community

00:27:51.030 --> 00:27:53.170
that we're building,
of as Chris said,

00:27:53.170 --> 00:27:55.810
this work that feeds us, right.

00:27:55.810 --> 00:27:58.400
Because at any moment,
even in logistical things

00:27:58.400 --> 00:28:03.830 position:56%
that could get tiresome or annoying,
we've got a ton of work to look

00:28:03.830 --> 00:28:07.560
at that inspires us and
reminds us of what we're doing

00:28:07.560 --> 00:28:09.760
and what we're trying to build.

00:28:09.760 --> 00:28:11.060
So I don't know that --

00:28:11.060 --> 00:28:13.960
and the interesting thing is as
