01:04:16.430 --> 01:04:18.660
You can touch me.

01:04:18.660 --> 01:04:21.020
I've been so good.

01:04:21.020 --> 01:04:24.860
I have been especially
still, all this time,

01:04:24.860 --> 01:04:29.290
each of my palms made a
bed for your untucking.

01:04:29.290 --> 01:04:34.460
Me, the meal made from
reused chicken grease,

01:04:34.460 --> 01:04:37.610
eased and always saying yes.

01:04:37.610 --> 01:04:44.290
Gender is cunning; the ruination
unwitting -- a stolen position.

01:04:44.290 --> 01:04:51.640
I have been bent over, the
beast dug out of me, the jewels.

01:04:51.640 --> 01:04:56.140
Pleasure light pops the eyes,
obsidian sticks in the throat,

01:04:56.140 --> 01:04:58.530
even this body doesn't register.

01:04:58.530 --> 01:05:04.550
The knuckles fold toward Lake
Michigan, the gut hardens,

01:05:04.550 --> 01:05:10.910
oxalate builds in the kidneys,
the tongue is a grateful peasant.

01:05:10.910 --> 01:05:14.320
For a beating I can
answer to a middle name.

01:05:23.730 --> 01:05:27.400
This poem is called
"At the Lavender Farm."

01:05:28.950 --> 01:05:34.030 position:56%
Fingers already spent, but lingering
on my hips, a sexual pal obsessed.

01:05:34.030 --> 01:05:39.520
We travel down past the docks,
take rest on a patch of grass.

01:05:39.520 --> 01:05:42.910
The batik print cloth
is laid out beneath us,

01:05:42.910 --> 01:05:47.850
our beers leaving footprints,
rings, sloppy circles

01:05:47.850 --> 01:05:51.890
of a local Wisconsin brew we
are happy to designate home.

01:05:51.890 --> 01:05:56.330
We enact our slovenly myth-making,

01:05:56.330 --> 01:06:01.220
the hybrid names we leave our
children, something Russian,

01:06:01.220 --> 01:06:06.020
something Ebo [assumed spelling],
the natural meanings queered.

01:06:06.020 --> 01:06:09.120
Your voice momentarily
dulcet, you edge the sentiment

01:06:09.120 --> 01:06:12.240
and ask me to love you forever.

01:06:12.240 --> 01:06:17.330
I swallow, my mouth sour, say,
"Ask me something difficult."

01:06:17.330 --> 01:06:21.440
It's here we love pretending
to be old,

01:06:21.440 --> 01:06:25.680
love twisting this coaxial
longing into reality.

01:06:25.680 --> 01:06:27.430
We are trying.

01:06:27.430 --> 01:06:30.770
No one else we know
is this gullible.

01:06:30.770 --> 01:06:35.270
Around us the lavender stocks run
the risk of being too beautiful.

01:06:35.270 --> 01:06:39.570
At dusk they, too, seem
to embody their condition.

01:06:39.570 --> 01:06:44.080
The smell of purple,
another kind of useless joy.

01:06:44.080 --> 01:06:48.680
Hair nestled on your
chest, stroking scars.

01:06:48.680 --> 01:06:51.530
I understand the risk of excess.

01:06:51.530 --> 01:06:55.800
I sniff your tufts of armpit
hair because I adore your musk.

01:06:55.800 --> 01:07:01.560
I've left myself, [inaudible] as
generously as how much I gift you,

01:07:01.560 --> 01:07:05.090
perhaps an evidence that
I am always this easy.

01:07:05.090 --> 01:07:08.740
If I am mewing on your
behalf, scold me better.

01:07:08.740 --> 01:07:13.720
The moon meets us, its carmine
fate is trite, tomorrow,

01:07:13.720 --> 01:07:19.360
returning to exile draws new
lust and brings us to our feet.

01:07:19.360 --> 01:07:24.920
We toe the spume of the lake,
the water an impossibility.

01:07:24.920 --> 01:07:27.880
My hand at the back of your
neck, I want to remind you

01:07:27.880 --> 01:07:31.790 position:56%
for our sake, nothing good is banal.

01:07:40.570 --> 01:07:45.020
This poem is a little gross, so I
hope you guys will bear with me.

01:07:45.020 --> 01:07:46.620
Not too bad.

01:07:46.620 --> 01:07:49.380
It's called "Deer Head."

01:07:50.480 --> 01:07:56.640 position:56%
Fall has unleashed its yellow, love
a solace extenuated from its bearer.

01:07:56.640 --> 01:08:00.840
On my afternoon walk,
alone this season,

01:08:00.840 --> 01:08:03.620
I come to the elementary school.

01:08:03.620 --> 01:08:08.820 position:56%
There in the butterfly garden a deer
head rides on its carnal prolixity,

01:08:08.820 --> 01:08:12.890
