places, dark color ablated

01:08:12.890 --> 01:08:17.860
by November's hard sun,
white bone exposed.

01:08:17.860 --> 01:08:21.390
I'm drawn to its sickness,
flies and all,

01:08:21.390 --> 01:08:24.490
the fetid odor leaning in to speak.

01:08:24.490 --> 01:08:30.080
My hand finds its muzzle,
mandible exposed, the hanging offal

01:08:30.080 --> 01:08:33.250
where the carcass has been severed.

01:08:33.250 --> 01:08:36.380
Prone to uttering absolutes,
I say nothing is more natural

01:08:36.380 --> 01:08:38.720
than this, and remain undeterred.

01:08:38.720 --> 01:08:44.630
Your eyes still intact and
expressive, I arrive honest

01:08:44.630 --> 01:08:48.910
with my desperation, my
claim unsophisticated.

01:08:48.910 --> 01:08:54.390
Buck, I am the son you want,
my own eyes thick as amulets,

01:08:54.390 --> 01:09:00.160
the hard edges of me cloven, all
of these tensions bifurcated.

01:09:00.160 --> 01:09:03.620
With opportunity, I would not
have left you in such uneasy rest,

01:09:03.620 --> 01:09:07.050
dead with the solitude
of lesser creatures.

01:09:07.050 --> 01:09:10.820
As most progeny may
attempt eventually,

01:09:10.820 --> 01:09:14.530
your decomposition is now
a lesson for my grief,

01:09:14.530 --> 01:09:18.870
the distress of my medic
souvenir of identification.

01:09:18.870 --> 01:09:22.330
We two flexing the
fiction of temporality,

01:09:22.330 --> 01:09:27.260
our time that cannot be
broken, this image of us.

01:09:27.260 --> 01:09:29.920
Around your antlers curl
newly-bloomed clematis,

01:09:29.920 --> 01:09:34.220
and I am reminded that this
month later it will snow.

01:09:34.220 --> 01:09:37.870
My head and yours will
be blanketed, washed.

01:09:48.000 --> 01:09:50.460
"I Used To Be Called Olivia."

01:09:50.460 --> 01:09:56.990
