01:43:37.790 --> 01:43:40.580
"Hunting Words with My Father."

01:43:40.580 --> 01:43:43.460
One morning I burst into
my father's study and said,

01:43:43.460 --> 01:43:46.270 position:56%
"When I grow up, I too want to hunt.

01:43:46.270 --> 01:43:50.220
I want to hunt words, and giraffes,
pictures, buffalos, and books."

01:43:50.220 --> 01:43:54.740
And he, holding a pen and a cup
of tea said, "Little Father,

01:43:54.740 --> 01:43:56.190
to hunt words can be dangerous.

01:43:56.190 --> 01:43:58.820
But still, it is best
to start early."

01:43:58.820 --> 01:44:03.030 position:56%
He waved his blue pen, and his
office turned into Nyandarua forest.

01:44:03.030 --> 01:44:06.770
It was morning, the mist rising
from the earth like breath as rays

01:44:06.770 --> 01:44:09.730
from the sun fell hard on
the ground like sharp nails.

01:44:09.730 --> 01:44:11.380
"Little Father, do you see him?"

01:44:11.380 --> 01:44:13.870
my father asked "No," I said.

01:44:13.870 --> 01:44:15.170
"Look again.

01:44:15.170 --> 01:44:16.470
The mist is a mirror.

01:44:16.470 --> 01:44:17.770
Do you see him?"

01:44:17.770 --> 01:44:19.070
And I looked again, and there
was a Maasai warrior tall

01:44:19.070 --> 01:44:20.810
as the trees, spear in hand.

01:44:20.810 --> 01:44:23.620
"Shadow him, feign him,
feign his movements,

01:44:23.620 --> 01:44:26.430
shadow him until his
movements are your movements."

01:44:26.430 --> 01:44:28.960
Running my feet along the
leaves, I walked to where he was,

01:44:28.960 --> 01:44:35.780
crouched like him so close to
the earth, feet sinking deeper

01:44:35.780 --> 01:44:39.390
into the earth as if in mud,
turning and reading the wind,

01:44:39.390 --> 01:44:42.580
and fading into the mist until
I become one with the forest.

01:44:42.580 --> 01:44:45.930
For half a day we stayed
like this, tired and hungry.

01:44:45.930 --> 01:44:50.240
I was ready for home, but my father
said, "I did not say this was easy.

01:44:50.240 --> 01:44:52.950
You cannot hunt words
on a full stomach."

01:44:52.950 --> 01:44:55.940
And just as soon as he spoke, there
was a roar so loud and stomping

01:44:55.940 --> 01:44:58.820
so harsh that hot underground
streams broke open like a dozen

01:44:58.820 --> 01:45:03.090
or so water pipes, sending hissing,
steaming water high into the air.

01:45:03.090 --> 01:45:06.310
I turned to run, but the
warrior stood his ground.

01:45:06.310 --> 01:45:09.360
As the roar and thunder came
closer, his hair, braided and full

01:45:09.360 --> 01:45:11.410
of red ochre, turned
into dreadlocks --

01:45:11.410 --> 01:45:15.730
dreadlocks so long that they seemed
like roots running from the earth.

01:45:15.730 --> 01:45:17.250
When the transfiguration
was complete,

01:45:17.250 --> 01:45:20.450
before me stood a Mau Mau
fighter, spear in one hand,

01:45:20.450 --> 01:45:21.920
homemade gun in the other,

01:45:21.920 --> 01:45:25.510 position:56%
eyes so red that through the mist
they looked like hot molten cinders,

01:45:25.510 --> 01:45:28.980
the long dreadlocks a thousand thin
snakes in the wind, the leaves,

01:45:28.980 --> 01:45:31.520
and the grass, and
thorns rushing past him.

01:45:31.520 --> 01:45:32.820
"You must help him.

01:45:32.820 --> 01:45:36.070
Don't just stand there, help
him," my father implored.

01:45:36.070 --> 01:45:39.400
But just as soon as I had closed
my little hands into fists,

01:45:39.400 --> 01:45:42.870 position:56%
the lion appeared high up in the
air, body stretched the whole length

01:45:42.870 --> 01:45:44.680
as the Mau Mau fighter
pulled the spear

01:45:44.680 --> 01:45:46.990
like it was a long
root from the earth.

01:45:46.990 --> 01:45:49.930
The lion, midair, tried to
stop, recoiled its talons

01:45:49.930 --> 01:45:51.730 position:56%
to offer peace, but it was too late.

01:45:51.730 --> 01:45:55.370
And he let out another roar as
his chest crushed into the spear,

01:45:55.370 --> 01:45:58.270
breastplate giving way until
the spear had edged its way

01:45:58.270 --> 01:45:59.900
into the heart.

01:45:59.900 --> 01:46:03.750
Dying, then dead, it continued
its terrible arc, and landed.

01:46:03.750 --> 01:46:06.580
I waved, and the picture
stood still.

01:46:06.580 --> 01:46:09.690
My father came up to me and asked,
